record.description:
                The requested page not found becuase Action Controller is has not created. You can solve the issue by applying any of follwing methods:

	<h3>1. Create an Action Controller</h3>
	Action Controller is a PHP class generally we create it in following location or inside in related component. This name of the file is same 
	as you used in the URL like {arg0}.php.
	<pre>/development/controllers/{arg0}.php</pre>

	An Action controller looks like bellow example. The class name must have a post fix "Controller" and extend to appRain_Base_Core for example <strong><em>{arg0}Controller </em></strong>
	<pre>class {arg0}Controller extends appRain_Base_Core
{
    public $name = "{arg0}";
    public $dispatch = Array(
        'preDispatchExclude' => array(),
        'postDispatchExclude' => array()
    );

    /**
     * Function Call before Page action method each time
     */
    public function __preDispatch()
    {
    }

    /**
     * Function Call before Page action method each time
     */
    public function __postDispatch()
    {
    }
}</pre>
<h3>2. Rout Page path</h3>
Your can edit router setting to load other page in this URL. Router configuration is available in following location.
<pre> /development/definition/uri_manager/page_router.xml</pre>
Create a new role and set Actual and Virtual path. Like follwing example
<pre>{lt}role{gt}
  {lt}ractual{gt}{arg0}/{arg1}{lt}actual{gt}
  {lt}rvirtual{gt}my_new_page_path{lt}/virtual{gt}
{lt}/role{gt}</pre>

<h3>2. Enable 404 setting</h3>
You can enable 404 page setting and set the new location of this page. It will help you to handle all broken page. <br /><br />

First login to admin panel and set the 404 page path in follwing location
<pre>Preference/Configuration/404 Page</pre>
Enter "/" to redirect in home page.<br /><br />

In same configuration page set the "Debug mode" 0(Zero) in following location
<pre>Preference/Configuration/Debug Mode</pre>

                The requested Model is not found. A model is a PHP class that connect to database and perform all data related activity. Follow bellow steps to create a model.

	<h3>Step 1. Create Database Table</h3>
	First create database table "{arg2}{arg1}". Always use table prefix in table name. Generally plural from of word is used in table name, for example "members" not "member". <br /><br />
	The database table must have a filed called "id" as a primary key with auto increment. 

	<h3>Step 2. Create Model file</h3>
	Create model file in follwing location 
	<pre>/development/models/{arg1}.php</pre>

	<em>Note: If you are creating the model for a component then create the file inside component directory and register the model accordingly. </em>

	<h3>Step 3. Create Model Class</h3>
	The class name must have a post fix "Model" and extend to appRain_Base_Model for example <strong><em>{arg0}Model </em></strong>
	<pre>class {arg1}Model extends appRain_Base_Model
{
    /**
     * Version mantain a track for Installer
     * Increase value when new SQL node added
     */
    public $version = "0.1.0";

    /**
     *
     * Use same as file name.
     */
    public $name = "{arg0}";

    /** 
     * Do not use prefix.
     *
     * User lower case
     *
     * Use plural form of the word 
     * For example: if model is Member then table name "members"
     */

    public $db_table = "{arg1}"; 

    /* Validation Map - Optional */	
    protected $model_validation = Array();

    /* Call Back Function - Optional */
    protected function _beforeSave($send = NULL)
    {
    }

    /* Call Back Function - Optional */
    protected function _afterSave($send = NULL)
    {
    }

    /* Call Back Function - Optional */
    protected function _beforeDelete($send = NULL)
    {
    }

    /* Call Back Function - Optional */
    protected function _afterDelete($send = NULL)
    {
    }

    /* Call Back Function - Optional */
    protected function _onValidationSuccess($send = NULL)
    {
    }

    /* Call Back Function - Optional */
    protected function _onValidationFailed($send = NULL)
    {
    }

}</pre>
